description:
Ultimate Comics Ultimates Volume 1

After the events of the Ultimate Avengers vs. New Ultimates mini-series, The Ultimates return once more, now as part of the "Ultimate Comics" line. Reed Richards has been left for dead following the events of Ultimate Comics Doomsday. Now, with the help and resources of Children of Tomorrow, he vows to solve everything. The republic is burning, and in response to this a new team of Ultimates is formed.

The series ended with issue 30 and was continued in the Hunger mini-series and Cataclysm: Ultimates and Cataclysm: The Ultimates' Last Stand mini-series.

Collected Editions

  • Ultimate Comics Ultimates by Jonathan Hickman vol. 1 (#1-6)
  • Secret Wars Prelude (#4)
  • Ultimate Comics Ultimates by Jonathan Hickman vol. 2 (#7-12)
  • Ultimate Comics: Divided We Fall, United We Stand (#13-18) along with Ultimate Comics X-Men (#13-18) and Ultimate Comics Spider-Man (#13-17)
  • Ultimate Comics Ultimates By Humphries vol. 1 (#18.1 & 19-24)
  • Ultimate Comics Ultimates: Disassembled (#25-30)
name: Ultimate Comics Ultimates

description:
English translation of the Japanese manga Dōbutsu no Kuni (どうぶつの国).

Orphaned after her parents were killed by Lynxes, Monoko is the only tanuki (raccoon dog) in her village without a family, until she finds a human baby in a river. In Animal Land, a world inhabited solely by animals, this human child is a mystery. This baby is Monoko's only chance at having a family and she is determined to raise the human child as her own. Animal Land is a quirky story about Monoko and the mysterious human baby.
name: Animal Land

deck:
It’s 1899, and the cusp of a new century in Ireland. 18-year-old Róisín Sheridan harbours ambitions to become a rival of the magnificent English actress Ellen Terry, if she can persuade her father that a career on the stage is ladylike.
Her plans are destroyed one horrific evening when she and her parents are viciously attacked by Abhartach: a neamh-mairbh who has been released after 1,400 years in the ground.
To survive and seek revenge Róisín must take up a new calling, one determined by ancient Gods whos
